<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 7:31PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A line of weakening thunderstorms will impact portions of Fergus,
Blaine, eastern Hill and northeastern Chouteau Counties through 800
PM MDT...
At 730 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking weakening thunderstorms
along a line extending from Havre to 11 miles southeast of Lewistown.
Movement was east at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Havre, Lewistown, Chinook, Harlem, Winifred, Grass Range, Parker
School, Beaver Creek, Hays, Azure, Agency, Fort Belknap, Roy,
Sangrey, St. Pierre, Fergus, Forestgrove, Rocky Boy, Cleveland and
Zurich.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
